name: Regent St.

description: {'Information': ["The London Dungeon is a spooky interactive experience that takes visitors through London's dark and gruesome history, with live actors, thrilling rides, and special effects."], 'Main Features': ['Educational, yet creepy insight into London’s darker past.', 'Thrilling rides (e.g., the "Torture Chamber" and "Drop Dead").', 'Scary themed rooms and interactive sets.', 'Live actors portraying historical characters.'], 'Visiting Tips': ['Book tickets online for discounts and to skip the queues.']}

name: London eye
description: {'Information': ["The London Eye is a giant observation wheel on the South Bank of the River Thames, offering stunning views of the city's landmarks such as Big Ben, St. Paul's Cathedral, and Buckingham Palace."], 'Main Features': ['360-degree views, 32 sealed glass passenger capsules, an iconic London landmark, interactive experiences, and VIP pods.'], 'Visiting Tips': ['Visit at sunset or night for breathtaking views of the city lights.', 'Book tickets in advance to skip the lines.']}

name: Hyde Park

name: Oxford Street
description: {'Information': ['Oxford Street is London’s most famous shopping destination, stretching 1.5 miles with over 300 shops, department stores, and flagship brands.', 'It attracts millions of visitors annually and is a key part of London’s retail and cultural scene.'], 'Main Features': ['World-famous shopping, department stores (Selfridges, John Lewis), flagship fashion brands, seasonal lights, and easy access to public transport.'], 'Visiting Tips': ['Visit on weekdays to avoid weekend crowds.', 'Use Oxford Circus or Bond Street stations for convenient access.', 'Take breaks in nearby cafés or Hyde Park for relaxation.']}

name: Georgian Parliament Building
description: {'Information:': ['The Georgian Parliament Building is located in the city of Kutaisi, Georgia, about 4 km west of the Colchis Fountain.'], 'Historical importance:': ['The building was opened in 2012, and is considered one of the most prominent modern architectural landmarks in Kutaisi.'], 'The most prominent landmarks:': ['Architectural design: Designed by Spanish architect Alberto Capo, it is characterized by its design inspired by the Salvador Dali painting, as it looks like the eye that monitors the surface.', 'Glass Dome: The huge glass dome contains gardens distributed over two levels and offices with glass facades.', 'Parliamentary Hall: In the heart of the building, there is a semi -white, white circular hall, which is made entirely of natural wood.'], 'working hours:': ['Visitors are allowed to visit the building during the official working hours, from Monday to Friday, from 9:00 am to 6:00 pm, and it is recommended to verify the working hours before the visit, as it may change.']}
short_description: The Georgian Parliament Building in Kutaisi is characterized by its modern architectural design and amazing glass dome.

name: Edgware Road

It is famous for its strong Middle Eastern influence, with numerous Lebanese, Egyptian, and Persian restaurants, shisha cafés, and Arabic shops.', 'The road is also home to historic landmarks, modern developments, and a lively nightlife scene.'], 'Main Features': ['Authentic Middle Eastern cuisine, shisha lounges, Arabic supermarkets, bustling nightlife, historic landmarks, and a mix of traditional and modern attractions.'], 'Visiting Tips': ['Best visited in the evening for a vibrant atmosphere.', 'Try famous restaurants like Maroush, Al Arez, or Beirut Express.', 'Be mindful of traffic; the area can be busy, especially on weekends.']}
